\f0\b\fs28 \cf6 \
REQUIREMENTS
\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 \
I omit details description because that is not only a programming task but also a DESIGN task, so it is up to you which methods/fields your classes will have. And generally, which classes you will have :) Required are: 
\f4\i\b \cf4 User, Employee, Teacher, Manager, Student, Admin, Course, Mark, Lesson, Researcher, ResearchPaper, ResearchProject
\f3\b0 .
\f1\i0 \cf2  Other classes are up to you.\
\

\f0\b\fs28 \cf6 Your system must support:
\f1\b0\fs24 \cf7 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab560\li720\fi-720\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf7 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Lesson type - lecture/practice\cf8 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cf7 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Student - bachelor. \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab560\li720\fi-720\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf8 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}4th year students have a research supervisor who is a Researcher. If a person whose h-index < 3 is assigned as a supervisor, a custom exception must be thrown. 
\f0\b \cf7 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab560\li720\fi-720\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0 \cf7 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}There can be more than 1 instructor per course \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab560\li720\fi-720\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf8 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}In the system, Teachers and Students CAN be researchers. Those teachers, who are professors 
\f4\i\b ARE always 
\f3\b0 researchers
\f1\i0 . However, bachelor students and teachers who are not professors(e.g., tutors, senior lecturers, etc.) 
\f0\b can 
\f1\b0 also be researchers. And there can be an employee, who is neither a Teacher nor Student, but he is a Researcher. Researcher has a research projects(s), research papers (also an Object!) etc.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Fields for a ResearchPaper can be chosen from here - https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/9766691 . Take 5-10 important ones, citations, name, authors, journal, pages, date , doi etc.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Researcher must have a method 
\f5\i PrintPapers(Comparator c) 
\f1\i0  that prints his research papers in sorted order, dictated by the comparator - by date published or by citations or by the article length (use pages).\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The system must support printing research papers of all researcher in the university, also sorted by date published or by citations or by the article length.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The system must support printing top cited researcher of the school, of the year (among all schools).\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}ResearchProject has a topic, published papers, and project participants. If someone who is not a Researcher tries to join the ResearchProject, custom Exception must be thrown.
\f0\b \cf7 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab560\li720\fi-720\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0 \cf7 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Report generation (about marks, just simple statistics)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab560\li720\fi-720\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \cb5 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
4 or more design patterns\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\partightenfactor0
